bio: My Name is Roberto Enrique Chavez Rodriguez. I am from Bolivia and I studied Information Technologies and Computer Science at Innopolis University, in Innopolis, Russia. I have work experience with frontend technologies such as JavaScript and ReactJS, and backend technologies such as Java and Spring. I am also very passionate about DevOps and I continuously look for ways to develop my skills in this field. My native language is Spanish, and I speak English and Russian as well. I am proactive, likable, friendly and totally willing to team up with anyone as to that is what is needed to get a task done. I consider myself as a good team player.

name: Adel Zakirov
headline: ML | AI enthusiast | Machine upbringer
creator: True
bio:
First things first:

I am happily married, have a daughter and a son, and black Labrador

I am playing acoustic guitar, like sailing and sometimes write blogposts about computer vision.. 

That’s my favorite meme/joke – https://i.redd.it/aqikqeae7gz61.jpg

I have worked both in academia and industry, corporations and start-ups, as a researcher and a team leader. AI is my passion. I am able of building end-to-end deep learning solutions myself, as well as set up a team and develop machine learning strategies in the company. I have done a lot with my own hands, so I have expertise on the technical side. I have led deep learning teams, so I have experience in team management.

name: Nicolas Guelfi
headline:
Professor at University of Luxembourg   ||
  Chief Executive Officier & co-founder at Right On Skill
creator: False
bio:
I am currently full professor at University of Luxembourg. I was recruited in 1999 to contribute to the creation of the university. I founded the Laboratory for Advanced Software Systems at University of Luxembourg which I directed for more than 10 years. I have been member of the ERCIM (European Research Consortium in Mathematics and Informatics) executive committee and I have founded the ERCIM Working Group on Rapid Integration of Software Engineering Techniques and the ERCIM Working Group on Software Engineering for Resilient Systems. I was acting as expert for the courthouse of Luxembourg concerning trials on conformance questions for 10 years. I have contributed to the field of software engineering as a researcher by publishing articles, editing books, acting as program chair or reviewing committee member. My  research contribution has mainly focused on: requirements definition and specification using formal, semi-formal or informal methods; and system dependability and resiliency. My current main field of research is development methods for deep learning. I also have been at the head of the creation of the new academic bachelor in Computer Science at the University of Luxembourg which opened in 2017. 
I am in the process of creating an education offer in the fields of Artificial Intelligence, Data Science and Software Engineering targeting industry needs in new talents hiring, up-skilling in re-skilling to face the current digital disruption.

headline: Professor – Innopolis University
creator: False
bio:
I am an experienced software architect, designer, implementor, and team leader. 
I am specializing in programming languages and compilers. Developing compilers has been my favorite area for almost all my career. I consider myself as an experienced compiler writer and have some remarkable achievements in this field. An industrial-strength ISO compliant C++ front end compiler is among them.

I have extensive knowledge in programming languages’ theory and I am familiar with many programming languages. I have practical experience in all aspects of compiler development including lexical and syntax analysis, semantic processing, code generation and optimization. I participated in a number of successful compiler projects – both as a developer and as a team leader.

Специализация: Compiler design and development
Source Program Analysis
Programming Languages
C/C++, C#, Ada, Java, XML/XSLT/XQuery

name: Mohamed Elwakil
headline: Assistant Professor of Computer Science
creator: False
bio:
Dr. Mohamed Elwakil is an assistant professor at the Math, Physics & Computer Science Department of the University of Cincinnati – Blue Ash College. Before joining UCBA, he was a lecturer at the School of Informatics, Computing, and Cyber Systems of Northern Arizona University. 

He earned a Ph.D. in Computer Science from Western Michigan University, MS, and BS in Information Systems from Cairo University in 2011, 2005, and 200, respectively. 

Dr. Elwakil’s teaching experience spans fifteen years of teaching computer science and information systems courses at seven universities and colleges in four countries. He has taught a wide range of undergraduate and graduate courses using different modalities such as face-to-face, distance learning, and wide-area classroom.

The primary focus of Dr. Elwakil’s research is to develop formal methods and supporting tools to aid modeling, analysis, and debugging of computer software. In particular, he is working on deterministic replay and trace-based predictive analysis of message-passing concurrent programs. His work appeared in conferences/workshops such as ATVA, ACT, EASE and PADTAD, and in journals such as ACM TODAES. His doctoral thesis supervisor was Dr. Zijiang Yang. He was the recipient of the 2010 PADTAD best paper award and the WMU Teaching Effectiveness Award 2005-2011. He worked in projects supported by grants from the NSF and the ONR.

In 2015/2016, Dr. Elwakil was a postdoctoral researcher at Innopolis University, Innopolis, Russia, where he worked with Dr. Bertrand Meyer on static deadlock prediction in object-oriented applications.

name: Ruslan Saduov
headline: Head of Social Sciences Lab at Innopolis University
creator: False
bio: Ruslan Saduov holds a cum laude degree in Philology, Teaching, and Translation from Bashkir State University. For a decade, Ruslan Saduov has taught a number of academic courses at Bashkir State University: Academic Writing, Public Speaking, Business Communication, Forensic Linguistics, Translation, etc. He was a major designer and director of a Fundamental and Applied Linguistics Program. His research areas include multimodal texts (Russian comics), linguistic and cultural landscape, political and media linguistics, cross-cultural communication, translation criticism. Ruslan Saduov is an author of over 90 scholarly publications. Since 2008, he has provided professional translation and interpretation services as a consecutive and simultaneous conference interpreter.

headline: Business strategy | Digital transformation | Global marketing | Partnerships
creator: False

bio:
I am C-executive with decades of experience in fields of digital marketing and innovation management.
 
Current DX is not only about technologies as AI, ML, AR, blockchain, biometrics and automation tools like CRM, CMS, LMS and others. 
This shift is in business models and new markets, in tremendous change of customer experience, in necessity of change in corporate digital culture. My goal as an advisor or a Chief Digital Officer is to develop strategy, manage processes and foster possibilities to make these changes effective and profitable for company. 

I know how to make it after 500+ completed digital projects for Intel, Metlife, Haier, Rosatom, MINI and other respectful brands. 
I also know that we can co-create better ideas and solutions together, so let's grow our trusted network with experts in CX, HR & change management, innovations, tech developers and IT-systems integration.

creator: False

bio:
I am a software engineer interested in the application of formal techniques to build reliable software.

Specialities:
Software Engineering
Formal Methods
Concurrency
Deployment of formal methods in industry

The work conducted by Manuel Mazzara and his team in recent years focuses on the development of theories, methods, tools and programs covering the two major aspects of software engineering: the process side, describing how we develop software, and the product side, describing the results of this process.

name: Luiz Jonata Pires de Araujo
headline:
Senior Lecturer in Computer Science at the University of Lincoln &     
Data Engineering and AI/ML Tech Leader at Locallity Labs
creator: True
bio:
A Ph.D. in Computer Science at the University of Nottingham, UK, with recent work experience in teaching, researching, and doing students' supervision for the last five years in international universities. My courses and research focus on Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning applied to real-world problems, and the use of Data Science techniques to gain valuable insights from corporate data.

Before joining the academia, I worked as a Data Engineer at Northeastern Bank of Brazil, with five years of experience querying and analyzing data to support decision-making. My duties included gathering data from diverse systems and sources to identify bottlenecks in the company's credit process and identify suspicious activities or transactions. My experience also includes five years in the software development industry as a System Analyst and Developer.

I am a friendly and cooperative workmate, always accessible and open to opportunities to connect and contribute to the team. After living in three different countries, I have developed strong social and soft skills to collaborate and manage conflicts in culturally diverse workplaces. I believe that a positive environment plays an essential role in the corporation's success and the growth of its individuals.

name: Parmod Kumar
headline: Associate Faculty at Jiangxi University of Engineering, Xinyu, Jiangxi
creator: True
past_company_1: Hunan University of Humanities, Science and Technology
school_2: University of Verona, Verona, Italy (9-13 July 2018)
bio:
I am a qualified Engineer offering 20 years of cross-functional experience and presently working as an Associate Professor with the Department of Electronics and Information Engineering, Jiangxi University of Engineering, Jiangxi, China. I started my career as a Marine Engineer and worked with Mitsui OSK Lines and Chevron Shipping Co. LLC. I have worked with the School of Energy and Electromechanical Engineering, Hunan University of Humanities, Science, and Technology, Loudi City, Hunan, and Regenesys Institute of Management as a Senior Associate Faculty (Data Science program). I have also worked as a guest faculty (Assistant Professor) at Hawassa University, Ethiopia. Before this, I worked as an Assistant Professor at MWU, Ethiopia. These projects were funded by the German Educational Funding Program and the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP). At the same time, I advise MS and Ph.D. students and serve as a reviewer for various reputed international conferences and journals. I am passionate about listening and solving challenging problems.
For my academic and research credentials, please refer to my CV attached to my profile.
Honesty, integrity, and dedication are my core strengths, significantly contributing to my career growth. I look forward to taking up assignments with greater responsibilities and creating a landmark. If you are interested in learning more about my experiences or future collaborations, please get in touch with me at kumaparm@isu.edu, dr.p.kumar2019@gmail.com,  and my mobile (+86-15727374611).

name: Mikhail Sverdlov
location: Washington, District of Columbia, United States
headline: C-level Product manager with 13 years of experience in digital/offline, and over 17 in tech.         I do three things: Insight, Strategy and Products that people love
creator: False
school_2: Brandeis Collegiate Institute, Los Angeles, CA, USA
bio:
Product manager with 13 years of experience in B2C and B2B software development (web and mobile), and over 17 years in tech. 
▪️ An experienced executive and an inspiring and integrative leader, who launched educational products for the largest EdTech in Europe with 150k active students, created a partnership platform that reduced by 6 times the mutual settlements for a top telecom company with 100M clients and earned more than 800M+ revenue for a bank with over 1M clients at the age of 25. 
▪️ An innovative entrepreneur by Adizes PAEI Model. Launched 2 own start-ups from the ground up and wrote more than 100 articles.

I do three things: Insight, Strategy and Products that people love.

Working in the areas of Product and Business Development, International Business Administration for various industries:

- Financial Markets and Institutions
- Information Technology and Services
- Management Consulting
- Education/Non-formal education
- Research/Social Media/Marketing

and love to dig into customer problems and solve them with modern technology. 


Professional Skills:
Product management | Project management | Team management | Business development | Strategy |   Growth | Partnership | Design Thinking | Experience Innovation | Business Analysis | People & Change

Can easily integrate new and innovative technologies into business needs in a way to increase revenue: Data Collecting and Analitycs, AI, Machine learning etc.
Deep knowledge in payment systems (technical, legal, and business). Proven expertise and knowledge in Telecom, Banking, Retail technologies, Data and Analytics niche etc. 
Experience in creating business units from ground zero, high-level business development. Huge experience in starting up projects and leading them to commercial success.

Can align, lead, and grow product teams from 10 to 100 people.

Really love the fact that companies I’ve worked for produce software and solutions that have an impact on everyone’s lives.

Personal:
Emotionally stable (COVID proven), able to work productively in tough terms, mobile, highly motivated, focused on the financial results of the company and mission.

I enjoy meeting new people and hearing new perspectives. Reach out if you want to talk about emerging tech, creating software products, or yachting.

name: Nikolaos Mavridis
headline: MIT PhD, Academic & Consultant in AI / Data Science / Robotics, Startup Mentor, Innovator
creator: True
current_position: Academic & Consultant in Robotics and Artificiial intelligence
bio:
As Principal Data Scientist at the SAP Global Center of Excellence, I have applied my expertise in data science, machine learning, and artificial intelligence to help clients achieve their business goals and solve complex problems. I have over 15 years of experience in academic and consulting roles in robotics and AI, all the way up to Full Professor rank, working with numerous organizations and institutions around the world.

My mission is to catalyze education, research, and entrepreneurship in robotics and AI in the Gulf and the wider region, and to create effective integration with relevant technologies such as the Internet of Things, Big Data, and Smart Cities. I am also a startup mentor for the MIT Enterprise Forum, where I support and advise innovative ventures in various domains, such as virtual reality, serious games, interactive storytelling, and UAV-based construction. I hold a PhD from MIT, where I developed a conversational helping hand robot, and several certificates from MIT, LSE, and UC Berkeley. I am passionate about creating impactful and meaningful solutions that can benefit society and culture

name: Alexander Chichigin
headline: Software/ML Engineer
creator: False
bio:
Key strengths.

Problem solving. I've been successfully solving technical, organizational and communicational problems. The solutions I like best are embarrassingly simple and straightforward.

Documenting. With significant academia experience I understand the importance of conveying your ideas, not only the results. Working as a researcher I acquired the taste and the skills for documenting my work (in form of articles, guides or plain old comments).

Functional programming. I'm regular participant of ICFP Contest (http://icfpcontest.org) as a member of a distributed team NCPLUG. We develop in Haskell and put all the code on Bitbucket.

Parallel and concurrent programming. In 2011 me and a friend of mine took part in Intel Russia Acceler8 contest (https://software.intel.com/ru-ru/articles/contest-acceler8-2011-main). We employed Intel C++ Compiler, Treading Building Blocks library, automatic vectorization and intrinsics. We had sped up our solution by factor of 20 or so.

name: Vasilii Artemev
headline: Passionate about engineering that brings value
creator: False
school_1: Quantic School of Business and Technology
bio:
I am passionate about software architecture and engineering best practices. I focus on providing high quality systems in terms of performance, modifiability, and usability within project scope. I have broad experience with software development processes ranging from OpenUP to Scrum, Kanban, and Disciplined Agile Delivery. I excel at explaining complex technical concepts to non-technical audiences and sharing my knowledge via public lectures with up to 1000 people. I enjoy working on projects where I can ensure needs of end users are aligned with business goals.
I think that for an outstanding software engineer it is important to have a lot of practice with technology, critical thinking, communication and soft skills, ability to make informed decisions based on present goals.

name: Vyacheslav Lukin
headline: CTO & Co-Founder of YAi | Tech entrepreneur | UK Global Talent | Software Engineer | Deep tech | AI/ML
creator: True
bio:
I am a seasoned technology entrepreneur with a profound background in telecom and software engineering. My expertise spans tech innovations, AI/ML product management, and leading highly motivated teams of software and ML engineers. With a strong goal-driven, result-oriented, and "get things done" attitude, I have a proven track record in developing and delivering technologically complex projects focused on strategic deliverables and budget adherence.

As the CTO at YAi, I lead the technology development and adoption of best practices for working with large language models (LLMs) in a MarTech/AdTech SaaS startup. My entrepreneurial journey includes founding and scaling startups like Edge Vision and INVIAN, where I successfully managed multi-stakeholder initiatives, driving innovation and achieving measurable results despite challenging economic and political environments.

Specialising in the complete product lifecycle, from strategy and GTM positioning to deployment and maintenance, I excel in introducing best practices in software development and leading diverse technical and business teams. My experience spans both startup environments and large corporate settings, with a customer-first mindset and direct engagement at operational and senior levels, including C-level.

name: Azat Yakupov
headline: Data Architect, Lecturer at University and Head Of Data Laboratory,  Data Coach
creator: False
bio:
Currently, I am certified and experienced Data Architect and Data Engineer with IT skills in the next areas below
- Big Data
- Relational Databases
- noSQL and non-relational databases
- Clouds databases (AWS, Azure, GCP, Yandex)
- Data Governance, including Data Mesh
- Data Quality
- Data Management
- DataLakes, LakeHouses, Data WareHouses and modern Data Models 
- Data Science and Data Mining
- High Availability and High Loading storages and databases

In parallel, I am a Senior Lecturer at Kazan Federal University, developed and developing new modern data courses for School 21 (Sber company), Innopolis University, Gazprom-Neft company, Piano company etc. 
Every year I am teaching more than 300 students from different countries.
Was a participant of some online lectures and a lot of offline activities: 
- "AI for children" (https://youtu.be/CqjqtjCb3x4)
- "Big Data - Big Chaos" (https://youtu.be/nzpsMJ-tUwk)
- "Education for Piano company" (https://youtu.be/Y1d39AQiDco)
Participant a lot of Database and Big Data conferences at Moscow, London and Kazan. 
I am Head of the Data Laboratory at Kazan Federal University (ITIS).

My personal blog and Data Laboratory website is https://datalaboratory.one
My official Kazan Federal University WebSite Link is https://kpfu.ru/azat.yakupov?p_lang=2
My approved and verified official certificates are available by link https://www.credly.com/users/azat- yakupov.a3a56af4


Participant a lot of Database and Big Data conferences at Moscow, London and Kazan.

Lecturer at University for 5 courses
• Introduction into Relational Databases
• Advanced PostgreSQL Database
• Non-Relational Databases and Big Data
• Data Mining
• Advanced Data Mining

name: Waqas Nawaz
headline: Academic Professor | EPSRC Member (UK) | Data Scientist | AI and ML Researcher
creator: True
school_2: National University of Computer and Emerging Sciences
bio:
Waqas Nawaz is an Associate Professor at Islamic University Almadinah, Kingdom of Saudi Arabia. He received his Computer Science PhD degree from Kyung Hee University (South Korea) in 2015. He worked as a Post-Doctoral Fellow in the Institute of Information Systems, Innopolis University, Russia from 2015 to 2016. Afterwards, he joined Faculty of Computer and Information Systems, Islamic University of Madinah, KSA as Assistant Professor in 2016. His research interests include graph mining, social network analysis, databases, data mining, big data, image processing, and artificial intelligence.

Large Graph Mining, Data Mining, Big Data Analytics, Clustering, Image Processing, Computational Intelligence, Path Navigation, Crowdsource Datasets (OpenStreetMap), Databases

name: Andrei Lapin
headline: Senior Frontend Engineer at Hellobetter
creator: False
bio:
I'm a proactive software engineer and problem solver with more than 10 years being in the field mostly focusing on Web development, frontend, project architecture, development processes and engineering culture in general.

My experience is quite wide as I started my career working on low level things with C/C++ languages and then transitioned to web field learning python, javascript with connected technologies (react, redux, ssr, micro-frontends, etc)..

Right now I'm on a position of Senior Web Developer with the main responsibility to deliver front-end solutions but at the same time I always go beyond that:
- Feature development
- Architecture/solution design and leadership
- Domain ownership
- Support of engineering culture and processes
- Mentoring team members
- Hiring process

My key skills are problem solving and collaborative communication. I like and quickly learn new stuff, proactively drive projects and initiatives, able to figure out a collaborative solution that will satisfy all the parties (product, management, designers as well as other developers and stakeholders), can think ahead by looking on the system from the top to plan a scalable solution for the future.

I never stop on learning so as of now I'm pretty much in philosophy as well as interested in processes, healthy management and leadership. Discovering and supporting ideas on software quality, continuous delivery, traceability, scalability and reliability. Have being learning more facilitation techniques and working on soft skills. In a short span looking for a transition into more like EM / tech lead position.

name: Abdul-Razak Adam
headline: Software Engineer @ Microsoft | Fullstack | Typescript, React, C#, Azure DevOps, PowerShell,
creator: False
bio: As a Software Engineer at Microsoft, I leverage my skills in Azure DevOps Pipelines and PowerShell to streamline developer workflows within the Windows codebase. I also develop user interfaces that present build quality and manage code flow across the Windows codebase, utilizing React and C#. Previously, I developed extensions for Visual Studio and Visual Studio Code to enhance the productivity of Windows Engineers, created PowerShell scripts for testing Windows builds, and constructed Power BI dashboards for our services. I also have experience as a faculty intern at Ashesi University, where I conducted practical labs on R and RStudio for second-year students and supported the lecturer in developing course content, teaching materials, and grading tasks. >>> Skills >>>
- Training and deploying ML & DL models
- Setting up monitoring and dashboards
- Creating robust data pipelines and services

- Speeding up development environments
- Mentoring and tutoring on technical topics

>>> I love to discuss >>>
- Optimal storage and embeddings retrieval in ClickHouse
- LLM benchmarking in business domains
- Topology preserving embeddings encoding
- Rotation/translation matrix, keypoints detection: mapping from 2D into 3D
- Smoothing noisy predictions with Kalman Filter
- Shared GPU dev environment: what if there’s a lack of GPUs, how to schedule trainings?
- ML model as a service: monitoring, deployment, debugging. How to treat custom dependencies?
- WSI Melanoma classification and segmentation: How to feed >1GB image to a Deep NN?
